The paper deals with medical knowledge graphs and proposes a new truth discovery method to estimate the trustworthiness of knowledge triples. This involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also deals with data management and knowledge representation, which are relevant to the sub-category of databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper involves statistical analysis and modeling, which are relevant to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
